    '**Each switchgear section (cubicle/cell) contains:**\n\n**Breaker compartment:**\n- Drawout vacuum or SF6 circuit breaker on a cradle with wheels\n- Positions: Connected (service), Test (breaker operational but disconnected from bus), Disconnected (fully withdrawn)\n- Primary disconnecting contacts (stabs) engage automatically when breaker is racked in\n- Secondary disconnecting contacts (control wiring) also engage automatically\n\n**Bus compartment:**\n- Insulated copper or aluminum main bus bars running horizontally through the lineup\n- Bus rated for full short-circuit current (25–63kA)\n- Phase barriers between bus bars\n\n**Cable compartment (rear):**\n- Power cable terminations (stress cones for shielded MV cables)\n- Cable support brackets and grounding connections\n- Surge arresters may be mounted here\n\n**Instrument transformer compartment:**\n- Current transformers (CTs) on each phase — ratio matched to load and relay requirements\n- Potential transformers (PTs) for voltage sensing (metering and relaying)\n- Control power transformer (CPT) — provides 120VAC for relay power from the bus\n\n**Relay/control compartment (front, low-voltage section):**\n- Microprocessor protective relay (SEL, ABB, GE, Siemens)\n- Metering (amps, volts, watts, vars, power factor, energy)\n- Control switches, indicating lights, annunciators\n- Wiring terminals for external connections\n\n**Ground bus:** Continuous copper ground bar connecting all compartment enclosures.',
